==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|NL.|Onchocerca|pos=a genus of parasitic worms}}, from {{der|en|grc|ὄγκος||barb}} + {{m|grc|κέρκος||tail}} + {{affix|en|-iasis}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ɒŋkəsɜːˈkaɪəsɪs/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|onchocerciases}}

# {{lb|en|pathology}} A disease caused by a [[worm]] of the genus ''[[Onchocerca]]'', especially as transmitted to humans by flies and often causing [[blindness]]; common in tropical Africa.

====Synonyms====
* {{l|en|river blindness}}
* {{l|en|Robles' disease}}

